    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix E1 Setup Failure handler in CU-UP\n\n### Summary\nThe E1 Setup Failure handler in the CU-UP (`e1apCUUP_handle_SETUP_FAILURE`) was not properly processing failure messages from the CU-CP. When an E1 Setup Failure was received, the handler would immediately call `exit(1)`, terminating the entire gNB process instead of gracefully handling the failure condition.\n\nAdditionally, the handler was not decoding the incoming ASN.1 message properly, not extracting the failure cause information, and not notifying other components in the gNB about the setup failure through the ITTI messaging system.\n\nThis caused the CU-UP to be unable to respond appropriately to E1 setup failures, leading to zombie gNB processes that had to be manually killed.\n\nThe fix replaces the immediate `exit(1)` with proper error handling, adds message decoding using the existing `decode_e1ap_cuup_setup_failure` function, and sends an ITTI message to notify the RRC layer about the failure.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Replaced `exit(1)` with proper error handling in `e1apCUUP_handle_SETUP_FAILURE`\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Added proper decoding of E1 Setup Failure message\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap.c`: Added ITTI message notification for E1 Setup Failure\n"
}